@database NumericClass
@index "Classes.guide/Main"

@Node Main "RxMUI - Numeric Class"


Numeric class    @{"Index" link "Classes.guide/Main"} @{"Super" link "AreaClass.guide/Main"}
@{u}                                                             @{uu}

  You can't create Numeric class objects, but it's attribute and methods can be
  used with any of its subclasses.

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Attributes@{ub}

  @{fg shine}CheckAllSize@{fg text}
  B ISGN

  @{fg shine}Default@{fg text}
  N ISGN

  @{fg shine}Max@{fg text}
  N ISGN

  @{fg shine}Min@{fg text}
  N ISGN

  @{fg shine}Reverse@{fg text}
  B ISGN

  @{fg shine}RevLeftRight@{fg text}
  B ISGN

  @{fg shine}RevUpDown@{fg text}
  B ISGN

  @{fg shine}Value@{fg text}
  N ISGN

  WARNING: If Max-Min is -1, both at init time or after a set, the class will
  refuse to accept it (MUI would crash).

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Methods@{ub}

  @{fg shine}Decrease@{fg text}
  <delta/N>

  @{fg shine}Increase@{fg text}
  <delta/N>

  @{fg shine}ScaleToValue@{fg text}
  <scalemin/N>,<scalemax/N>,<scale/N>
  Direct only method.

  @{fg shine}SetDefault@{fg text}
  <value/N>

  @{fg shine}ValueToScale@{fg text}
  <min/N>,<max/N>
  Direct only method.

@EndNode
